# TRANSLATOR: Label for the recommended hardening value shown below an
# unhardened indicator. Appears as "[ Recommandé : <value> ]" in the TUI.
# Corpus: Termium Plus attests "recommandé(e)" as the fr_CA past-participle
# adjective form for "recommended". Masculine form used here to agree with
# "réglage" (setting, masculine noun) implied by the context.
# Visual check: single-line display string.
# "Recommended" = 11 chars; "Recommandé" = 10 chars — within 150% rule.
#: components/rusty-gadgets/umrs-ui/src/data_panel.rs:693
msgid "Recommended"
msgstr "Recommandé"

